[{"location":"library/all_index/","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"CurrentModule = Learn","category":"page"},{"location":"library/all_index/#Learn.jl","page":"Index","title":"Learn.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"library/all_index/","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"library/all_index/","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"Modules = [Learn]","category":"page"},{"location":"library/all_index/#Learn.Learn","page":"Index","title":"Learn.Learn","text":"This module is for exploration of Julia, Documenter and other interesting concepts.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"library/all_index/#Learn.add-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Index","title":"Learn.add","text":"add(x, y)\n\nReturns x + y\n\nExamples\n\njulia> x, y = Vector([1,2,3]), Vector([4,5,6]); add(x, y)\n3-element Array{Int64,1}:\n 5\n 7\n 9\n\njulia> which_sig(add, x, y)\n\"add(x, y)\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"library/all_index/#Learn.add-Tuple{Int64,Int64}","page":"Index","title":"Learn.add","text":"add(x::Int64, y::Int64)\n\nReturns x + y\n\nExamples\n\njulia> x, y = 1, 3; add(x, y)\n4\n\njulia> which_sig(add, x, y)\n\"add(x::Int64, y::Int64)\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"library/all_index/#Learn.add-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{T,T}} where T<:AbstractString","page":"Index","title":"Learn.add","text":"add(x::T, y::T) where {T<:AbstractString}\n\nReturns x*y\n\nExamples\n\njulia> x, y = \"my\", \"string\"; add(x, y)\n\"mystring\"\n\njulia> which_sig(add, x, y)\n\"add(x::T, y::T) where T<:AbstractString\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"library/all_index/#Learn.add-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{T,T}} where T<:Number","page":"Index","title":"Learn.add","text":"add(x::T, y::T) where {T<:Number}\n\nReturns x + y\n\nExamples\n\njulia> x, y = 1+3im, 3+5im; add(x, y)\n4 + 8im\n\njulia> which_sig(add, x, y)\n\"add(x::T, y::T) where T<:Number\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"library/all_index/#Learn.∑-Tuple{Vararg{Int64,N} where N}","page":"Index","title":"Learn.∑","text":"∑(x::Int64...)\n\nAdds all parameters:\n\nsum_i^n x_1 x_2 dots x_n forall x_k in mathbbN\n\nExamples\n\njulia> ∑(1,2,3,4,5)\n15\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"create_package/#Create-new-package","page":"Create Package","title":"Create new package","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"create_package/#Creat-from-template","page":"Create Package","title":"Creat from template","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"First add PkgTemplates","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"(@v1.5) pkg> add PkgTemplates","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"Then use the following template","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"using PkgTemplates\nt = Template(;\n    user=\"binnisb\",\n    julia=v\"1.5\",\n    plugins=[\n        Git(;manifest=true, ssh=true, jl=true),\n        Tests(;project=true),\n        GitHubActions(;x86=false),\n        Codecov(),\n        Documenter{GitHubActions}(),\n        Develop(),\n        Citation(;readme=true)\n    ],\n)\nt(\"Learn\")","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"Create the GitHub reopository Learn.jl and push master to it.","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"To be able to push the docs to GitHub pages, I needed to follow DocumenterTools.genkeys and create the deploy key and DOCUMENTER_KEY secret.","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/#Tests,-Documenter-and-doctests","page":"Create Package","title":"Tests, Documenter and doctests","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"The template above creates a GitHub Action to build the docs, and run doctest. Out of the box it actually couldn't run doctest with tests defined in doc strings in source files.","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"How I solved it:","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"First I created a docs/make_structure.jl which imports and setup what is needed for Documenter and doctest, and then two files docs/make_docstring.jl and docs/make.jl, where the former only runs doctest, and the latter runs doctest and builds and deploys the docs.","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"Both cases need some setup code, which lives in make_structure.jl and makes the Learn module available in all docstrings in the Learn module. If you create submodules, that might need some extra manipulations to get that working.","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"I also chaged the .github/workflows/ci.yml to call a file make_doctest.jl for running the tests, and then calling make.jl to build the docs and deploy.","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"Then from terminal:","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"# From the Learn.jl folder\njulia --project=docs  docs/make_doctest.jl  # Runs the Doctests\njulia --project=docs  docs/make.jl  # Builds documents and runs the Doctests\njulia --project=.  test/runtests.jl  # Runs the test suite for Learn","category":"page"},{"location":"create_package/","page":"Create Package","title":"Create Package","text":"should work.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Learn.jl","page":"Home","title":"Learn.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This package is intendet to gather my learnings and explorations using Julia.","category":"page"}]
